    {
      "id": "9d951ea2b55bb06485efc16102e4d09e21e5531c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-05-29 01:29:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "5e7dfc225398767137b77eee96150b79b917a7d0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-05-29 05:28:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\nThe patch itself looks OK, and unless under very special cases, the llog layout and size are the same as current.\n\nBut what I real worry about is the compatibility issues when downgrade to old release, and the inoperability issues with old client: keeping the log_log_hdr members as the original layout is necessary, but is that enough? can the old server/client can handle the case of \"bitmap > 8192\" properly? If possible, please add some tests.\n\nOn the other hand, does this patch will be some related with b_ieel3_0?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "efd69fe1779dc48d423ef92c1c4f9e718fc54060",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2015-05-29 05:33:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Verified-1\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.6/x86_64: (https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/05a7d820-05c3-11e5-a9e1-5254006e85c2).  Ran 17 tests.  No failures in this session, but a previous session failed for this commit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "a1ac4f34c8fa7359dbca3a7443a5a50af8c8f8b7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2015-05-29 05:51:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change cannot be cherry-picked to master.\nPlease rebase the change locally and upload the rebased commit for review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "b79cfb73d48c694b38ba6a94ae775b2fa8e3dad5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-05-29 07:44:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThe latest version of this patch does not change the actual llog record size from 8KB, only changes the code so that we might do that in the future of needed. We thought it would be necessary to change the log record size to fix the DNE2 atripe count limit, but then we worked out a different method of storing the records in the llog and didn't need to increase the limit, since it would have caused interoperability problems as you wrote, and still wouldn't be able to be large enough. . \n\nAt least with this patch the limit can be increased in the future much more easily. The llog disk format was always planned to allow different record sizes, but the code didn't handle this case very well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "4e744c8be5e1bfb8d5dc6d64b386787508f80054",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-05-29 08:15:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nYes, that is why I gave \"+1\" to the patch since it does not really change current llog layout and size. I am working on the patch for renaming fsname on b_ieel3_0, I need to think about whether it will affect such tools in future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "7e710d69cc6657a639f6800761c6e02258facbea",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-06-05 17:41:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nYes, that is why I gave \"+1\" to the patch since it does not really change current llog layout and size. I am working on the patch for renaming fsname on b_ieel3_0, I need to think about whether it will affect such tools in future.\n\nThe idea is that, we will decide the chunk_size through log_header if the llog already exists. If the llog is new, the chunk_size will be gotten from the ctxt.\nfor downgrade, I think will unlikely change the current llog format, except the changelog, and it definitely need extra patch for older version if we want to support downgrade in this case.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "89f9fa80475134056265b65aeeeecf6963d7abf2",
      "author": {
